16:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Hive and Motion share a solid foundation of core features including Task Management, Ai Assistant, Calendar, Collaboration. Where Hive pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Notes and Templates, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Hive holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while Motion scores 8/10 overall and 7/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
17:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Hive offers a more budget-friendly entry point at Free, compared to Motion's starting price of $34/mo. Hive has a notable advantage here with its free plan, allowing you to get started without any financial commitment. Motion does not currently offer a free tier, which means you will need to pay from day one."}]]}]
